5. Turning to climate change, DOL40:18 writes: In 21st Century Malawi, the Kingdom of Heaven will be on earth in the fullest possible sense. If there is any Bible prophecy that could seem to apply to our time, we might consider that this 21st Century is a ‘time of the Gospel’.[17] This is consistent with DOL40:13, which says: ‘On April 3, 2003, the Lord Jesus Christ gave me Jeremiah 1:11-12, where today, there is an economic battle taking place between those with progressive visions and those with backwards visions. President Bingu wa Mutharika is in the progressive camp. Anti Globalization Movement (AGM) President, George Kondowe, is in the backward camp.’ Furthermore, DOL13:4 writes: We went to South Africa and attended a centennial [100 years] anniversary of Makumila Church of Scotland in a township (the very first church there), in Jubilee Church choir, they taught us one of their favorite hymns, ‘To God be the Glory’.
